<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Skivbolaget</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/album.css">
    <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/5fc0d582b6.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>

<body>
    <%- include ("header.ejs") %>
    <div class="container" id="albumcontainer">
        <div class="item">
            <div class="image">
                <img src="<%= album.imgUrl %>" alt="Image of '<%= album.name %>' by <%= album.artist %>" />
            </div>
            <div class="artist"><%= album.artist %></div>
            <div class="album"><i><%= album.name %></i></div>
            <div class="year"><%= album.released %></div>
            <div class="price">
                <form action="/addtocart/<%= album._id %>" method="get">
                    <button type="submit"><%= album.price %> SEK</button>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="albumInfo">
        <div class="musicPlayer">
            <iframe src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/album/0xtOxVRRaA0kW7X4PlbtuP" width="100%" height="380"
                frameborder="0" allowtransparency="true" allow="encrypted-media"></iframe>
        </div>
        <div class="curator">Curator</div>
        <div class="curatorsNote">
            <p>Lorem Ipsum is the single greatest threat. We are not - we are not keeping up with
                other websites. Lorem Ipsum best not make any more threats to your website. It will be met with fire and
                fury like the world has never seen. Does everybody know that pig named Lorem Ipsum? An ‘extremely
                credible
                source’ has called my office and told me that Barack Obama’s placeholder text is a fraud.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="aboutAlbum">About album</div>
        <div class="albumInfo">
            <p><%= album.description %></p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>